Description: Stamp (vessel): qisṭ. Four line Kufic inscription. Made of green glass.
Curator's comments: The name of the commodity seems to begin with two 'Iāms', most probably 'li'- preceding the definite article. What follows may be 'ʿayn' or a 'tooth-letter' followed by 'jīm'. Another 'tooth' and then final 'rāʾ' or nūn appear to follow.
Bibliographic references: Morton 1985 / A Catalogue of Early Islamic Glass Stamps (128)
Associated names: Named in inscription: Yazīd b. Abī Yazīd
